U.S. Stock-Index Futures Trim Early Losses as Euro Rebounds From Day’s Low

-- B y   M i c h a e l   P .   R e g a n
-- 
2011-07-12T12:04:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-12/u-s-stock-index-futures-trim-early-losses-as-euro-rebounds-from-day-s-low.html
U.S. stock-index futures pared
declines as the euro trimmed earlier losses and the bonds of
 Europe ’s most indebted countries recovered from an earlier
slide.  Futures on the Standard & Poor’s 500 Index lost 0.4 percent
to 1,312.80 at 8:01 a.m. in  New York  after tumbling as much as
1.8 percent earlier. The euro slipped 0.2 percent to $1.3997,
rocovering from as low as $1.3837. Italian 10-year bond yields
were up four basis points at 5.72 percent after topping 6
percent earlier.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
